<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>About · The Open Stacks</title>
  <meta name="description" content="About The Open Stacks · a free, open-access radical library. No accounts, no tracking.">
  <meta name="theme-color" content="#c8392b">
  <link rel="icon" href="/logo.svg" type="image/svg+xml">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@300;400;500;600&family=Crimson+Pro:ital,wght@0,400;0,600;1,400&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://kit-pro.fontawesome.com/releases/v7.0.0/css/pro.min.css">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/style.css">
</head>
<body>
<%- include('_nav', { showSearch: false }) %>
<main class="book-page">
  <div class="book-page-inner">
    <a href="/" class="back-link">← Library</a>
    <h1 class="book-title" style="margin-bottom:1.5rem">About The Open Stacks</h1>
    <div class="body-text">
      <p>The Open Stacks is a free, open-access library of radical, anarchist, anti-fascist, and political texts. Knowledge has always been a tool of power · we're giving it back.</p>
      <p>We archive texts that are at risk of being taken down, deplatformed, or simply forgotten. Anarchist theory, anti-fascist history, labour movement documents, feminist and queer liberation writing, and more. If it threatens the powerful, it belongs here.</p>
      <p><strong>Against fascism. Against capitalism. Against all forms of oppression.</strong></p>
      <p>Over <strong><%= stats.total ? stats.total.toLocaleString() : '—' %></strong> texts indexed across <%= stats.sources || '—' %> source collections. <strong><%= stats.withBody ? stats.withBody.toLocaleString() : '—' %></strong> with full text readable directly in your browser · no download, no account needed.</p>
      <h2>Use it</h2>
      <p>No accounts. No tracking. No ads. Take what you need. Everything is open source and self-hostable. Translate any non-English text to English directly in the browser · free, no API key required.</p>
      <p>Texts remain © their authors and under each source's terms. We keep copies of what's at risk. Take what you need, give what you can.</p>
      <h2>Contribute</h2>
      <p>Drop a Markdown file into <a href="https://github.com/taynotfound/open-stacks-library" target="_blank">the data repo</a>, push, and it appears here automatically. Every item credits its origin · nothing is hidden or claimed as ours.</p>
      <h2>API</h2>
      <p>
        <code>GET /api/search?q=&amp;category=&amp;page=</code> · search the collection<br>
        <code>GET /api/book/:slug</code> · single book metadata<br>
        <code>GET /api/stats</code> · collection stats<br>
        <code>GET /feed.xml</code> · RSS feed<br>
        <code>GET /opds.xml</code> · OPDS catalog for e-readers<br>
        <code>POST /api/translate/mymemory</code> · free translation proxy<br>
        <code>POST /api/translate</code> · Google Translate proxy
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</main>
<%- include('_footer', { stats }) %>
</body>
</html>
